Description:
Create the Dream in the College Zone
An irresistible renovator, this rare 2 bedroom 2-storey Art Deco one of a pair is a fairytale opportunity to make it this delightful home something magical again. Retaining its classic ceilings, this homely retreat enjoys an entry foyer with loads of storage, a charming lounge, sun filled dining room with French doors onto a paved north facing courtyard garden; a retro 70s kitchen with electric stove, central bathroom, separate toilet, a large laundry and a lock up garage. The uniqueness of this home means the two lovely bedrooms (BIRs) are upstairs, yet feel connected with the home. With so much potential to add your cosmetic taste, change the layout and even extend, it's a fantastic vision to make it beautiful again. An excellent unit alternative with no common land, it's superbly located in the McKinnon Secondary College zone, around the corner from McKinnon Village, the train and Joyce Park, walk to North Road eateries and buses to Monash University.

Description:
Stylish Courtyard Living with a Feeling of Space
Enjoy access into your own beautifully landscaped courtyard garden in this sparkling 2 bedroom 2 bathroom ground floor apartment.
Radiant with porcelain tiles, this open and airy retreat features an entry hall from the common foyer, generous tiled open plan living & dining area with a superb granite kitchen (Bosch dishwasher), 2 double bedrooms (BIRs), 2 brilliant bathrooms (ensuite) and a European laundry.
The courtyard is east-facing and has a beautiful blend of honed bluestone paving, Lilydale topping and raised garden beds that create lovely privacy, making it an ideal place for a BBQ gathering with friends.
In this boutique group, this idyllic first home, downsizer or investment provides R/C air conditioning, video intercom and lift access to the secure basement car space and the lockable store room.
In this leafy street, one block from the fabulous North Road shops, cafes and wine bars, Ormond station, Kilvington Grammar and buses to Monash University.
As this is the first time the property has been offered for sale and it is less than 5 years old you may be eligible for the first home owners grant. Please make your own enquiries to see if you are eligible for the governments $10,000 grant.

Description:
Large In Living, Luxury & Quality In The Zone
Architecturally designed to provide every contemporary requirement, the exceptional appeal of this luxurious town residence is enhanced by its sophisticated style, easily managed attitude and exclusive Ormond Hill position.
Impressive space and superb finishes are revealed throughout its light-filled dimensions, where spacious open-plan living/dining detailed with built-in cabinetry, stained glass windows and timber floors unfolds to a private north-facing courtgarden with fishpond and retractable awning creating a peaceful setting for outdoor entertaining.
A modern kitchen with feature splashback, Smeg/Bosch appliances and stone surfaces serves in style, whilst 3 robed bedrooms (main with ensuite), bathroom and upper-level retreat heighten a sense of space.
Brilliantly appointed with ducted heating, split system AC, ducted vacuum, video intercom, powder room, ample storage, single garage and car space.
Prestigiously located in one of Ormonds finest within the McKinnon College zone, minutes to McKinnon Road shopping village, train station, and excellent primary schools. ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER

Description:
Renovate & Revive or Redevelop & Reward - STCA
Ready to renovate, easy-to-extend and perfectly positioned for your new home project, this 2-bedroom Californian Bungalow comes with healthy prospects, College zone benefits and a lifestyle location.
Timelessly preserved with an open fireplace for both formal rooms and a detailed backdrop of high ceilings, original light switches, lovely leadlight and ready-to-reveal Baltic Pine floors, this classic interwar home features granite benchtops in the timber kitchen, a frameless screened shower in the dual access bathroom and a mud room beside the laundry/WC.
With 581sqm approx. of big blank canvas rear gardens with a carport out front and the comforts of ducted heating and cooling within, this versatile block provides a solid base for a prestige renovation, and a rewarding rental return whilst you plan.
Best of all, it has everything youll need in close proximity including Joyce park, Centre Rds vibrant shopping strip, McKinnon Reserve and Secondary College and a fast commute to Chadstone or Southland.
ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER.

Description:
Private, secure & superbly located
Bright, warm and welcoming, this sun-filled lock up and leave apartment enjoys an easily accessible ground floor position within a secure and stylishly updated group. Just moments to North Roads burgeoning shop, cafe and bar scene along with Ormond station, buses to Monash University and a choice of parks - it could not be better located than this! Freshly painted throughout, the apartment features a large eat-in kitchen with quality stainless steel appliances (including a dishwasher) along with lots of cupboard and preparation space. Providing plenty of room to stretch out and unwind at the end of the working day, the lounge opens out to a sunny oversized courtyard perfect for catching up with friends on the weekends. The queen-sized bedroom boasts built-in robes and is serviced by a bright bathroom (with room for laundry appliances) and separate WC, whilst split system heating/cooling, intercom and covered parking space on title are all offered. Sure to pique the interest of busy professionals and young home buyers, this fabulously carefree abode is also certain to attract the attention of those looking to secure a stress-free investment in a popular and highly sought-after locale.

Description:
A Treasure Trove of Land and Promise
First time on the market in 85 years, this rambling 3 bedroom Californian Bungalow on approximately 655sqm is excited about its future, especially with its rear access to Fraser Street. With so much originality to admire from the high strapped ceilings to the plate ledges, deep sills and leadlights, there's plenty to repurpose or revive in this classic home. Welcomed by a double door entry, this intriguing charmer features a wide hallway, 3 large bedrooms (2 with BIRs), a delightful lounge, adjoining dining room (potential OFP), vintage kitchen, central updated bathroom with cast iron bath and a rear vestibule. There's a cottage style laundry with separate toilet in the west-facing rear garden plus an oversized double garage and pedestrian access to Fraser Street. With potential to renovate, rebuild or redevelop (STCA), it's complete with security doors, ample storage and gas heating. A heartbeat to North Road shops, cafes and restaurants, Ormond station, Monash University bus and the beautiful EE Gunn Reserve.
